### 1. VirtualHost Configuration File
(
# 1. Navigate to the sites-available directory
cd /etc/apache2/sites-available/
# 2. Copy the existing template file to create your new 'priyam.conf'
sudo cp 000-default.conf priyam.conf
# 3. Open your newly created file to make your modifications
sudo vim priyam.conf
)
(/etc/apache2/sites-available/priyam.conf)
```apache
<VirtualHost *:443>
ServerName www.priyam.com
DocumentRoot /var/www/html
SSLEngine on
SSLCertificateFile www.priyam.com.pem
SSLCertificateKeyFile priyam.key
SSLCACertificateFile rootCA.crt
</VirtualHost>
```
### 2. Main Apache Configuration (/etc/apache2/apache2.conf)
```apache
ServerName www.priyam.com
```
### 3. Local Hosts File (/etc/hosts)
```text
127.0.0.1 www.priyam.com
192.168.74.74 www.priyam.com
```
## 4
# Edit global apache configuration
cd /etc/apache2
sudo vi apache2.conf
# Map the IP addresses locally
sudo vi /etc/hosts
# Enable SSL module, enable the site, and reload the service
sudo a2enmod ssl
cd /etc/apache2/sites-available
sudo a2ensite priyam.conf
sudo systemctl reload apache2
```
### 5. Browser Verification Steps
```text
Firefox -> Settings -> Search for "certificate" -> Manage Certificates -> Authorities -> Import ->
rootCA.crt (Check Trust options) -> Okay
Navigate to: https://www.priyam.com
```
